The paper proposes a new approach for training deep generative models for graph-structured data with node labels. This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, specifically in the sub-field of generative models. The paper also mentions the use of the approach in image generation, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision. Additionally, the experiments involve various types of graph datasets, such as citation networks and protein graphs, which could be related to social networks and bioinformatics, respectively. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The sub-categories cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible due to the nature of the datasets used in the experiments.
